<style type="text/css">
td {
    padding:0 5px 0 15px;
}

table {
    border-collapse: separate;
    border-spacing: 0 1em;
}

#myButton {
  margin-top: 3px;
  float:right;
}
</style>

<p id="notice"><%= notice %></p>


<div class="row">

  <div class="col-md-8">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-6">
        <h1 style="line-height: 0px;">Listing Videos</h1>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-6">
        <%= link_to "New Video", new_video_path, type:"button", id:"myButton", :class => "btn btn-primary new-video-btn"%>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-8">
    <table  class="table table-striped header-fixed">
      <!-- <thead>
        <tr>
          <th colspan="3"></th>
        </tr>
      </thead> -->
      <tbody>
        <% @videos.each do |video| %>
          <tr class="spaceUnder">
            <td> <%= image_tag(video.attach_video.url(:thumb)) %> </td>
            <td> <%= video.attach_video_file_name %></td>
            <td><%= link_to 'Show', video %></td>
            <td> | </td>
            <td><%= link_to 'Delete', video, method: :delete, data: { confirm: 'Are you sure?' } %></td>
          </tr>
        <% end %>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="panel-group" id="accordion" role="tablist" aria-multiselectable="true" style="margin-top: 14px;">
    <div class="panel panel-default">
      <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="headingOne">
        <h4 class="panel-title">
          <a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseOne">
            Introduction
          </a>
        </h4>
      </div>
      <div id="collapseOne" class="panel-collapse collapse in" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingOne">
        <div class="panel-body">
          Video has become one of the most common sources of visual information. But, as the amount of video data is daunting and the number of videos is rapidly increasing â€” 72 Hours of video are uploaded to YouTube every 60 seconds and it takes over 82 years to watch all videos uploaded to YouTube per day! we need a tool to summarize videos. A tool that aims to compactly depict the original video to make a shorter watchable video with the important events presented in a shorter period of time. 
          
          In our project, we implemented one of the ways of video summarization using Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) to model the variable-range temporal dependency among video frames, so as to derive both representative and compact video summaries.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


</div>
</div>

